Nigeria Deposit Insurance Corporation said on Thursday in Kaduna that it has fully paid both insured and uninsured depositors of 18 failed banks in the country. NDIC Managing Director, Umar Ibrahim, disclosed this at the ongoing 41st Kaduna International Trade Fair organised by the Kaduna Chambers of Commerce Industries, Mines & Agriculture. Ibrahim said that creditors and shareholders of the closed banks had also been paid liquidation dividends to the tune of N4.987bn as of December 31, 2019. The NDIC boss, who was represented by the corporation’s Director Communication and Public Affairs Department, Sunday Oluyemi, said, “NDIC has fully paid all the depositors of 18 closed Deposit Money Banks all their monies (both insured and uninsured) that were trapped in such banks. “Creditors and shareholders of the closed banks had also been paid liquidation dividends to the tune of N4.987 billion as of 31st December 2019. “In the same vein, I am delighted to disclose that the Corporation has developed the Framework for the extension of Deposit Insurance cover to the tune of N500,000 per depositor for depositors of Payment Service Banks.” 